to your company, Michael.

118
00:05:38,492 --> 00:05:40,687
- And say good-bye to these.
- No, no, no, no.

119
00:05:40,794 --> 00:05:44,059
<i>So Michael was understandably</i>
<i>anxious about their reunion.</i>

120
00:05:44,164 --> 00:05:46,359
Guess I do get to see them again, huh?
[Chuckles]

121
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:50,369
Can we please have one conversation
that's not about my rack, Michael?

122
00:05:50,471 --> 00:05:52,769
- Yeah.
- Maybe a better question would be...

123
00:05:52,873 --> 00:05:54,704
what evidence do I have
against you, because...

124
00:05:54,808 --> 00:05:56,708
No, no, no. I don't...
I don't wanna know.

125
00:05:56,810 --> 00:05:59,108
I just want to know
what you want.

126
00:05:59,213 --> 00:06:01,704
I'd like to be in charge
of the Bluth Company.

127
00:06:01,815 --> 00:06:05,046
Well, I want a hamburger and French fries,
but I can't have the bun or potatoes. Get real.

128
00:06:05,152 --> 00:06:08,644
